# Coding Standards

## TypeScript

- Strict mode. No `any` unless truly unavoidable — prefer `unknown` with narrowing.
- Use `type` for object shapes and unions; `interface` only when extending is needed.
- Prefer `const` assertions and discriminated unions over string enums.
- Named exports over default exports.

## React

- Functional components only. No class components.
- Use `useCallback` / `useMemo` for handlers and derived values passed as props.
- Colocate component-specific hooks in the same file or a sibling `use*.ts`.
- Prefer controlled components; use `useRef` for imperative DOM access (especially FigUI3 web components).

## State (Zustand)

- All canvas mutations go through `dispatch(createEvent(...))`. Never mutate store state directly.
- Use `useAppStore` selectors for reads; avoid subscribing to the entire store.
- Transient/high-frequency state (drag, resize) belongs in `transientStore`, not the main store.

## Styling

- Tailwind utility classes for layout and spacing.
- Figma design tokens via CSS custom properties (`--color-bg-*`, `--color-text-*`, `--color-border-*`).
- FigUI3 web component styles are scoped inside `.figui3-scope` using `figui3-scoped.css`. Use CSS `@layer` for import, then unlayered overrides for specificity.
- Base font: Inter, 11px. Tailwind `text-xs` and `text-base` both resolve to 11px.
- Font weight `normal` = 450, `medium` = 550.

## Gen-AI Controls

- The `specWithCurrentValues` pattern stamps live control values into `props.defaultValue` before persisting `genAiSpec`. This is the single source of truth for control state.
- `genAiValues` JSON is a fallback only.
- When a control's action modifies fills, always preserve the existing fill type — never hardcode `type: "solid"`.
- Use `fill` (type `"fill"`) for any gradient or multi-stop color control. Reserve `color` for single solid colors only.
- Chat history is scoped per frame ID (`chatHistoryMapRef` in `useGenAI.ts`). Each frame gets its own conversation context.
- Auto-generate is one-shot: empty history in, no history stored out. Prevents contamination of follow-up prompts.
- `CustomControlsSection` accepts `objects: CanvasObject[]` (multi-selection). The "+" button dispatches `"gen-ai-auto-generate"` events.
- AI shimmer (`setAiEditingObjectsGroup`) wraps all LLM calls in `runGenAiWithChat`. The star icon animates when `aiEditingGroups` overlaps the selection.

## Naming

- Components: PascalCase (`CustomControlsPopover.tsx`)
- Hooks: `use` prefix (`useGenAI.ts`)
- Utils/adapters: kebab-case (`action-adapter.ts`, `fill-converter.ts`)
- CSS files: kebab-case, colocated with their component
- Store files: camelCase (`transientStore.ts`)
